# Image formats

Never use WebP on this site — it makes images look blurry.

## Format rules

| Asset type | Format |
|------------|--------|
| Photographs (site photos, avatars, logos, personal photos) | **JPG** |
| Vectors, 3D renders, sketches, UI screenshots, diagrams, text | **PNG** |

## Workflow

1. Export from Figma as PNG (frame nodes, not raw fills) so crops match the design.
2. **Use the full-width frame node** at `@4x` scale — not the smaller thumbnail frame in a 3-up row. At 2xl (1440px container), full-width images need ~4800px source for retina sharpness.
3. Save photos as `.jpg`, graphics as `.png` under `public/images/`.
4. Run `node scripts/optimize-images.mjs` — PNG capped at 4800px wide, JPG at 3200px (never WebP).

## Adding new assets

- Update `PHOTO_BASENAMES` or `PHOTO_PREFIXES` in `scripts/optimize-images.mjs` when a new photo doesn't match existing patterns.
- Do not add WebP conversion or `crop` fields in components — fix cropping at export time.
